The President of the United States addressed a group of mayors in the East Room of the White House. He thanked them for their hard work and praised their efforts in their respective cities. He announced that the Department of Justice is taking action against sanctuary cities that violate federal law by releasing criminal aliens back into communities. He emphasized the importance of public safety and criticized mayors who choose to boycott the event. The President also discussed the achievements of his administration, including job creation, tax cuts, and infrastructure investment. He highlighted the decrease in unemployment rates for African Americans and Hispanics, and the increase in investment by companies such as Apple. The President expressed his commitment to supporting local government and rebuilding the country's infrastructure. He also mentioned the importance of reducing regulations and streamlining the approval process for construction projects. The President concluded by expressing his confidence in the future of the country and thanked the mayors for their leadership and partnership.